                            <comment id="16071857" author="tomasflobbe" created="Mon, 3 Jul 2017 02:17:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached two log files. They are full of messages like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;o.a.s.c.ChaosMonkey monkey: selected jetty not running correctly - skip&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16071934" author="tomasflobbe" created="Mon, 3 Jul 2017 05:23:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not sure yet why it started failing like this recently (maybe related to the legacyCloud changes?). Looking at the code that emits that message, not sure what&apos;s the intention of it: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/blob/master/solr/test-framework/src/java/org/apache/solr/cloud/ChaosMonkey.java#L406-L430&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/blob/master/solr/test-framework/src/java/org/apache/solr/cloud/ChaosMonkey.java#L406-L430&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
It looks like we get a random Jetty and then expect the leader core to be in it, but that&apos;s not necessarily the case. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16317624" author="tomasflobbe" created="Tue, 9 Jan 2018 03:28:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve been testing with this patch. I haven&apos;t seen the same error again. The test is still not 100% reliable, and I can get it to fail beasting it with tests.nightly=true&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
